description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to for a Stop Smoking Service Specialist to join a newly developed stop smoking service in Sunderland. This role involves working as part of the specialist stop smoking team in a clinical and strategic role to develop and provide stop smoking advice, counselling and support to NHS patients and clients in a variety of settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Stop Smoking Service Specialist will be a Registered General Nurse with significant post-registration nursing experience, as well as experience as a stop smoking advisor, with experience of running groups or clinics. The successful candidate will also have practical knowledge of public health work, training and teaching experience and an understanding of smoking cessation theories and practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Stop Smoking Service Specialist will work with the Stop Smoking Service lead nurse to deliver stop smoking support throughout the service area according to national and local standards and to lead the delivery of training. The successful candidate will be required to project manage their own workload, and be the lead for long term conditions within the Stop Smoking Service, co-ordinating and driving work in hospital and primary care settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will make a significant contribution to the improvement of health and wellbeing of target groups and individuals in Sunderland. This will include the continued development of the specialist stop smoking service and smoking cessation programmes, including training and support of a network of NHS providers of stop smoking support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will be enthusiastic and self-motivated, have excellent communication and interpersonal skills and the ability to work on their own initiative and as part of a team. The post holder will work flexibly to the needs of the service, which include out of hours working, including evenings and weekends and some regional travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional knowledge acquired through degree supplemented by diploma level specialist training, experience, short courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RGN qualified&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NMC registered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Mentor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trained in motivational interviewing or coaching (or willingness to undertake this training).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant post-registration nursing/midwifery experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a stop smoking advisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in public health work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaching/ training experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of running smoking cessation groups/clinics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and implementing systems and structures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of evidence-based practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaching/training qualification e.g. ENB 998 or C&amp;G 730.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Counselling qualification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualification in public health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in specialist health promotion/public health work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing systems and structures with partner agencies outside their own.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Irving&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public Health Strategy &amp; Programme Manager&lt;/p&gt;
